<br>
DC PET NO HASTE: Upon chanter landing mez, DC pet would 98% of the time tell it's owner it could not wake the target.  The times it could wake the target were the SAME times it's quad roll was already being processed when mez hit.  Meaning 1 of the 4 attacks had hit the mob before mez, thus making the other 3 come after the mob was mez'ed.<br>
<br>
DC PET WITH HASTE:  Upon chanter landing mez, DC pet would 80% of the time tell it's owner it could not wake the target.  The rest of the time fell under the same as the above.<br>
<br>
Mage pet Unbuffed:  Same as DC with no haste.<br>
<br>
Mage pet BO IV'ed: around a 90% unable to wake mob. The rest of the time, same as previouse.<br>
<br>
Epic pet with chanter haste: held a 85% unable to wake mob.  The rest of the time same as previouse.<br>
<br>
To those that would deny DS as a mez breaker:<br>
<br>
DS'ed epic with /pet hold on:  Had a 5% mez break.<br>
<br>
DS'ed melee with attack off: broke mez about 1% of the time<br>
<br>
This difference is obviously due to the ac between melee and pet.<br>
<br>
No blues were harmed in this process, chanter tashed before mez'ing on all mobs and only had 3 resisted mez's.  <br>
<br>
If it's a text bug, then I would LOVE to know how a txt bug can break a mez.  Mobs that roll an attack as they are slain still carry out their attack on the way down.<br>
<br>
You have slain priest of zek.<br>
tank has been completely healed.<br>
priest of zek was burned.<br>
priest of zek hits tank for 167 points of damage.<br>
priest of zek was burned.<br>
priest of zek hits tank for 100 points of damage.<br>
<br>
Might be a txt bug, but the melee didn't take the damage until AFTER priest of zek was on the ground.  Can a txt bug also make hit points dissapear after a mob dies?  This was an actual message we recieved in kael, and there were several WTF's floating around in raid channel so it wasn't my lag.  Notice melee CH'ed after mob died, then care to explain why melee was missing 265hp's by the time he opened his inventory screen?  Must have taken him 12 seconds to think to open it, after being repeatedly asked to.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
You still don't believe in mid swings? Then why is it several melee can hit inbetween your pets quad?  Why is it several monks/warriors/pets can quad at the same time (more often the monks) but the txt from the quads mixes them up?  If swings were instant then upon a sucessful quad roll you WOULD see all 4 attacks in sucession without interuption of ANY kind, then the next melee's quad's txt would come.  <br>
<br>
As melee is:<br>
MonkA punches for 76<br>
MonkA punches for 57<br>
MonkB punches for 88<br>
MonkA punches for 40<br>
CasterA begins to cast a spell.<br>
MonkB punches for 87<br>
MonkA Punches for 44<br>
MonkB punches for 40<br>
MonkB punches for 85<br>
<br>
If quad rolls were instant as some of you tend to believe:<br>
MonkA punches for 76<br>
MonkA punches for 57<br>
MonkA Punches for 44<br>
MonkA punches for 40<br>
CasterA begins to cast a spell.<br>
MonkB punches for 88<br>
MonkB punches for 87<br>
MonkB punches for 40<br>
MonkB punches for 85<br>
<br>
You will NEVER see the second scenario as happen, hence quad rolls are not instant. <br>
